<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1184,1788,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead box="[136,1184,1788,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyStep box="[136,1184,1788,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">1a. Fruit elliptic to suborbicular, strongly angustiseptate silicles; ovules 6−14 per ovary; seeds uniseriate.</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1451,1817,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1817,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
2a. Plants pubescent; fruit valves smooth; petals 
<quantity box="[644,742,1817,1839]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1−1.5 mm</quantity>
long; at least some leaves pinnatifid .................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1321,1451,1817,1839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="andraeana">
<emphasis box="[1321,1451,1817,1839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. andraeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
2b. Plants glabrous to subglabrous; fruit valves conspicuously reticulate; petals 
<quantity box="[939,1019,1846,1868]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2−3 mm</quantity>
long; all leaves usually entire ....................... ........................................................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1321,1451,1875,1897]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humistrata">
<emphasis box="[1321,1451,1875,1897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. humistrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1239,1904,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead box="[136,1239,1904,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyStep box="[136,1239,1904,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">1b. Fruit oblong or linear, subterete or slightly angustiseptate siliques; ovules 20−70 per ovary; seeds biseriate.</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
3a. Fruit oblong to ellipsoid, 
<quantity box="[455,554,1932,1954]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2−2.5 mm</quantity>
wide; ovules 20−40 per ovary; cauline leaves broadly spatulate to obovate, 3−5-lobed........... .................................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Edginton, Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" box="[1287,1451,1961,1983]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="queenslandica">
<emphasis box="[1287,1451,1961,1983]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. queenslandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1278,1990,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead box="[136,1278,1990,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
3b. Fruit linear, 
<quantity box="[329,445,1990,2012]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="0.6">0.6−1.4 mm</quantity>
wide; ovules 50−70 per ovary; cauline leaves narrowly oblanceolate, (3−)5−15-lobed.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
